  "interpretation": "The isolated down_proj row is fast when repeated on constant input, but it slows to the same band as the full tail-MLP chain whenever a gate_up+GeGLU producer runs immediately before it, even if down reads the separate constant input. Small constant input is not slower, so the gap is not explained by GeGLU numeric magnitude. The next bottleneck direction is cache/producer-state or weight-residency around the gate_up -> down sequence, not current Triton W4A16 or GeGLU data sensitivity.",
